Key Match Events: LeBron James recorded his second straight triple-double with 19 points, a season-high 16 assists, and 10 rebounds.
Anthony Davis scored 22 points before leaving with an eye injury in the third quarter.
Austin Reaves scored 27 points for the Lakers.
Chris Boucher and RJ Barrett scored 18 points apiece for the Raptors.
Immanuel Quickley scored 12 points and played back-to-back games in LA after missing eight straight with a pelvic bruise.
Jakob Poeltl had 14 points and 10 rebounds while playing well against Davis on both ends.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Lakers improved to 5-0 at home.
The Lakers beat Toronto for the second time in nine days.
The Raptors have lost four straight and eight of nine.
The Lakers have a winning record through 10 games for the first time in four seasons.
James has 13 triple-doubles since he turned 37 in December 2021. Only six other players in NBA history accomplished the feat after their 37th birthdays, doing it a combined eight times.
